{
  "texts": [
    "This is identified with the S-dual D5 ′ -type interface between O(2N) and SO(2N + 1) gauge theories [7].",
    "This can be realized as the orthogonal type orientifold projection of the D5 ′ -type interface between U(N) and U(N) gauge theories.The half-index of the SO(2N)|SO(2N + 1) interface of the D5 ′ -type takes the formII 4d SO(2N)|SO(2N + 1) D ′ (t; q) = 1 2 N -1 N!",
    "(q) 2N ∞ (q 1 2 t ±2; q) N ∞ N i=1 ds i 2πis i × i<j (s ± i s ∓ j; q) ∞ (s ± i s ± j; q) ∞ (qs ± i s ∓ j; q) ∞ (qs ± i s ± j; q) ∞ (q 1 2 t 2 s ± i s ∓ j; q) ∞ (q 1 2 t 2 s ± i s ± j; q) ∞ (q 1 2 t -2 s ± i s ∓ j; q) ∞ (q 1 2 t -2 s ± i s ± j; q) ∞ × N i=1 (qs ± i; q) ∞ (q 1 2 t -2 s ± i; q) ∞.",
    "(3.50)The integrand contains the expected contributions from the 4d SO(2N + 1) gauginos and scalar fields for x 2 > 0 which are not part of the SO(2N) gauge theory as well as the 4d SO(2N) gauge theory fields contributions.In fact, we have checked that the half-indices (3.47) and (3.50) precisely coincide with each other!",
    "The equality between (3.47) and (3.50) should imply the following duality of the interfaces:SO(2N)|USp(2N) NS5-type interface ⇔ SO(2N)|SO(2N + 1) D5 ′ -type interface."
  ]
